msgid "Help"
msgstr "Hilfe"

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:40
msgid ""
"Code Defenders pits two teams against each other on a Java class. Attackers "
"must create mutants in the code, whilst Defenders write unit tests to catch "
"(kill) these changes to the code."
msgstr ""
"Bei Code Defenders treten zwei Teams mit einer Java-Klasse gegeneinander an. "
"Die Angreifer müssen Mutanten im Code erzeugen, während die Verteidiger Unit-"
"Tests schreiben, um diese Änderungen am Code abzufangen (zu töten)."

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:41
#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/index.jsp:71
msgid "Defenders"
msgstr "Verteidiger"

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:42
msgid ""
"At the top of the page, there are two panels. On the left is the original "
"Class Under Test (CUT), and on the right there is a panel to write a new "
"test, along with a \"Defend!\" button which submits the test."
msgstr ""
"Oben auf der Seite gibt es zwei Felder. Auf der linken Seite befindet sich "
"die ursprüngliche zu testende Klasse (Class Under Test, CUT), und auf der "
"rechten Seite gibt es ein Feld, um einen neuen Test zu schreiben, zusammen "
"mit einer Schaltfläche \"Verteidigen\", die den Test absendet."

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:44
msgid ""
"Below these panels are two more panels, which show existing mutants and "
"tests. In the mutants panel, mutants can be claimed as being equivalent "
"(which is covered at the end of this page). Existing mutants can also be "
"seen by the icon present in the margin of the CUT panel."
msgstr ""
"Unterhalb dieser Tafeln befinden sich zwei weitere Tafeln, die bestehende "
"Mutanten und Tests zeigen. Im Mutanten-Panel könnten Mutanten als "
"gleichwertig deklariert werden (dies wird am Ende der Seite behandelt). "
"Vorhandene Mutanten sind auch an dem Symbol am Rand des CUT-Panels zu "
"erkennen."

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:46
msgid ""
"We're going to submit a test to kill an alive mutant. Tests don't "
"necessarily have to target alive mutants, and can simply be made to kill "
"possible future mutants."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:51
msgid ""
"If an error is made in your test and it does not compile, a full compiler "
"error is shown at the top of the screen. In this case, I did not add the "
"brackets at the end of a function call."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:53
msgid ""
"After re-submitting the test, we see that it compiled successfully and "
"killed the mutant."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:58
msgid ""
"The actual changes made in killed mutants can be viewed by clicking the "
"\"View Diff\" button on the killed tab of the mutants panel."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:64
#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/index.jsp:70
msgid "Attackers"
msgstr "Angreifer"

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:65
msgid ""
"The attack page only has two panels, existing mutants, and a panel "
"containing the CUT, which can be modified to create mutants. Green lines are "
"covered by existing tests, with darker green showing more coverage."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:67
msgid ""
"Similarly to tests, mutants are limited by rules, which come in three "
"strictness levels:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:71
msgid ""
"Here I have created a mutant by changing the > comparator to <. Return "
"values, variables, etc. can also be changed."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:76
msgid ""
"After submitting our mutant by pressing the \"Attack!\" button, we see that "
"it survived two existing tests. Similarly to submitting a test, an error "
"will be displayed if the mutated class did not compile."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:79
msgid "Equivalents"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:81
msgid ""
"It is possible to create a mutant which is identical in functionality to the "
"CUT, so no test can pass on the CUT and fail on the mutated class."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:82
msgid ""
"For example, the following functions are identical in behaviour, they are "
"equivalent:"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:87
msgid ""
"If a Defender believes that an Attacker's mutant is equivalent, they can "
"click the \"Claim Equivalent\" button on the mutant."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:89
msgid ""
"After this, the Attacker will see that their mutant was marked as "
"equivalent. If the mutant is equivalent, they should accept it as equivalent."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:90
msgid ""
"However, if the mutant isn't equivalent, the Attacker can prove that it "
"isn't by writing a test which kills it."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:93
msgid "Scoring System"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:94
msgid "Mutants"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:95
msgid ""
"For every test a mutant passes where the test executes the mutated line, the "
"mutant gains a point."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:96
msgid "Mutants also gain one point for being created and surviving."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:97
msgid "Tests"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:98
msgid ""
"For every mutant a test kills, the test gains points equal to the score of "
"the mutant."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:99
msgid "A test gains a point for killing a previously untouched mutant."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:100
msgid ""
"A test is also given an additional point for killing a newly created mutant."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:101
msgid "Equivalences"
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:102
msgid ""
"If an Attacker proves a mutant is not equivalent, they keep the mutant's "
"points and gain an additional point."
msgstr ""

#: /home/timlg07/CodeDefenders/src/main/webapp/jsp/help.jsp:103
msgid ""
"If the Attacker accepts the mutant is equivalent, or the game expires, they "
"lose the points of that mutant, and the Defender who claimed that it is "
"equivalent gains a point."
msgstr ""

